## Overview

Creates a new side antag that can support or hinder other antagonists in a shift. Appears both as a ghostrole antagonist and a rare chance to roll alongside other antags ( like thief )

## Background

Originally , we just goofed around when we realised this is turning out to be quite well designed. Then it snowballed into a fully fledged design doc!


# Core Gameplay Loop

## Progression

### SPAWNING MECHANIC-
This is intended to act as an entrance for midround ghostroles. Would probably be fine roundstart as long as sec/command play along.

- Spawn in a random maints locker (skeleton code, specifically maints though.) If shift start , forces person that rolled the antag to spawn in as an assistant.
- Other than the bag containing the kit picker, emergency box etc. the Doc gets:
- A visiting Doctor/Scientist/Roboticist PDA with an ID (randomly picked)
- Matching clothes for the ID 
- IC, they should be treated as a visitor with no hostilities from sec, making the beginning risk less. 
They can explore, role play and chat up potential clients. As a trade off, going through the visitor process with HoP will make them a likely suspect when chromed up gonks start showing up.
Alternatively, they can attempt to stay covert in maintenance, finding “clients” through intimidation or violence. This offers them anonymity and pairs well with the syndicate collaborator kit. It ups the risk as well, as a single slip up or an unlucky patrol can cause them to be taken to security for questioning, as a “visiting roboticist” would not be surgically implanting gas masks onto tiders. 
This setup offers a large range of approaches for different kinds of players and works at any point of the round.

#### 5 Tiers , each separated into detrimental and supporting implants. Implants are bought with RC , the Bodymodder starts with 20 RC and gains more via the following methods:

#### Tier 1 is 5 RC , Tier 2 is 10 RC , Tier 3 is 20 RC etc. ( doubles each tier )

Tier 1 and 2 are implants , both given and removed by just implanting and empty implanter ( Implant code )
Tier 3 and above require surgery ( To all implants in this tier mention which organ they replace!!! ) ( Shitmed organ code )

“RC” ( Research Credits ) gain:

- Detrimental implants give more RC ( 1 RC x Tier x 1 min )
- Supporting implants give less RC ( 1 RC x Tier x 5 mins )


To get RC , Ripperdoc needs to use their implant ( internal downloader , it can also recharge anything put into it,batons ,cells ,power cages , etc. ) to extract RC from clients after it builds up. This action heals ALL poison damage from clients and injects them with 10u multiver and 30u of grani. Each extraction makes it require a cooldown period of 60 seconds.
They can also use the downloader on research server to get 5 RC per researched tech. Steals 1 tech at a time with a 20 second doafter for each tech. ( ninja code? )

Possible objectives: ( Chooses 3 randomly )
Earn 100k or more spesos shift end
Have over 50 RC in your uplink shift end
Steal over 15 technologies
Escape alive and unrestrained
Have ( 20% of crew ) clients
Deploy Panopticon ( This antag's guaranteed, final goal )

Uses pinktext so no need to track if completed or not!



### Balance issues

The bodymodder might buff certain antags a lot , which may cause issues. As such close monitoring for balance will be required in the first weeks. Might be worked around by underlining in antag description that the Bodymodder is not to assist other antags in their objectives but to fulfill their own.

## Starting Equipment

#### Ripperdoc Shop (separate satchel from implants , once it is done buying just throw it away! Uses thief satchel code , stuff chosen spawns in a syndie toolbox), buy two or three abilities  to fit an archetype (cyberpunk ripperdock/ frankenstein like scientist/ biomodder etc.):

- Multiphase Mantis blade - Has an EMP/Stun/Kill mode , EMP has one charge per 40 seconds , Stun works like a stun prod that self recharges and kill deals armblade damage. (probably just an arm blade reskin/ possibly goob port)
- Antagonist cooperation kit ( Has a syndicate radio implant , a changeling hivemind radio implant and a voice mask ) ( Work with your Syndicate buddy, or (literally) break their legs in front of security for top 10 anime betrayal)
- Stem Cell Pen - for getting people up after implanting. ( Looks like a pen , has 2 charges that recharge once per 40 seconds , each charge works like a hypopen that injects 15u epi and 5u grani )
- Shock pads - Work like a defib but in combat mode can shoot out a projectile that deals 10 shock and forces target to go prone ( without stunning ). Has 1 charge for projectile and regains it over 60 seconds.
- Tranquilizer dart launcher ranged stun similar to the energy crossbow syndies can buy, doesn't deal damage, limited ammo that self recharges. Both deals stamina damage and injects target with 10u chloral hydrate. Stores 3 bolts.
- Syndicate surgery kit (should be free to make tier 3 implants feasible.)
- Black market digiboard - works like an EMAG-ed cargo console with some additional contraband thrown inside ( basic stuff like syndie guns and armour worth less than 20 TC with 1 TC being 1k spesos ). Can also buy “TC”  at an exchange rate of 1000 spesos for 1 “TC”. To actually buy anything it silently purchases them and sends them to ATS , where the clients or ripperdoc needs to pick them up.
- Rechargable DNA Scrambler - DNA scrambler that gets 1 charge every 5 minutes. Can hold 2 charges at once.
- Rechargable SCRAM implanter - SCRAM implant that holds 3 charges and gets one back every 1 minute.

# Implants
### All implants deal ( 0.05 x Tier-1 ) per second poison damage to person injected with them. Some may also have additional downsides. For IPCs , implants cause them to lose charge faster , requiring recharges more often!

