## Game Design Rationale

In anticipation of funkymeds new cybernetics system, the ripper will be the perfect antagonist to give it the time to shine. Who better to help with showing the new implant mechanics than dubious spess doctors? This antag will both allow antags to interact more with the surgery and body powers , but also give medical more work to do by making them remove harmful implants , harvest beneficial ones for crew from people working with the Bodymodder and heal those poisoned by the slowly growing poison damage of implant users!
### More antag and crew interaction!
The new implants have some seriously fun interactions possible for both crew and antags. A syndie traitor requesting an implant that lets them have a mantis blade but the ripperdoc adding a detrimental implant as well that activates in the worst moment. A crew member requesting pizza arms or a shoulder cannon and getting a femur breaker and MORE!


### Risk and reward for the crew!
An antagonist that helps the crew by supplying its members against threats while also helping the threats themselves would bring a lot of benefits. A syndie not killing their target because it will piss off the Bodymodder , or security staying blind to maints surgery because they themselves benefit from it! It would mean that people wouldn't instantly think "Antag = Arrest"! That doesn't mean they are not an antag - they will mind control people and in the end create a malfunctioning AI. Both their end goal and their brainwashed clients will be sure to provide plenty of conflict!

## Roundflow & Player interaction

### Roundflow
A ripper would not be the spotlight of a shift. While other antags create the tension, the maints doc supplies tools to both sides of the conflict while also reaping benefits for themselves, asking their clients for money, technology and Research Credits from their implants in return. While their most powerful implants may cause an antagonist to be more powerful, they might not supply them due to that ruining the Status Quo that allows the ripper to continue being ignored by sec! Making the implants contraband would also create tension between the Magistrate and HoS and the crew , with one side wanting to uphold the law and the other wanting more cybernetic enchancement! However, if the ripper is ignored for too long, allowing them to amass enough RC and "Willing clients", they might cause a malfunctioning AI to spawn, already supported by an army of cyborgs.


## Administrative & Server Rule Impact
Nothing added would cause reasonable strain upon the server. At most , it may be dubious how people interpret the T.I.D.E.R mood. But otherwise , a person who gets a cool implant will not become a free agent - likewise , an antag that gets chromed up won't suddenly become crew aligned. Normal mind control rules apply to "The Hook"

## Technical Considerations

We tried to underline what existing code can be used for the features! Hopefully it will help with coding it , as no features implemented here require anything groundbreaking while at the same time hopefully staying original!
